definition.value: A member of the class of pyrazines that is pyrazine in which three hydrogens at positions 2, 3 and 5 have been replaced by methyl groups.
A retinoid anion that is the conjugate base of 13-cis-4-oxoretinoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A cyclitol phosphate that is 5a-carba-beta-D-mannose having a (4S,8S,12S,16S,20S)-4,8,12,16,20-pentamethylheptacosyl)phosphate group at position 1.
A mannose phosphate consisting of beta-D-mannose having a (4S,8S,12S,16S,20S)-4,8,12,16,20-pentamethylheptacosyl)phosphonomethyl group at position 1.
A mannose phosphate consisting of beta-D-mannose having a (4S,8S,12S,16S,20S)-4,8,12,16,20-pentamethylheptacosyl)phosphono(difluoro)methyl group at position 1.

A branched amino tetrasaccharide consisting of an N-acetyl-alpha-L-quinovosaminyl-(1->3)-N-acetyl-alpha-D-galacturonosaminyl-(1->3)-N-acetyl-alpha-L-quinovosamine trisaccharide unit, the galacturonosaminyl residue of which carries a further N-acetyl-alpha-L-quinovosaminyl residue via a (1->4) glycosidic linkage. Corresponds to the tetrasaccharide repeating unit of the capsular polysaccharide of Vibrio vulnificus MO6-24.
